The paper discusses the implementation of a shallow GRU neural network on a low power micro-controller for automatic dietary monitoring. This involves machine learning techniques for audio event classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the practical application of this technology in the field of healthcare (cs.EM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of sensors and data analysis for monitoring human behavior (cs.SD) and the development of low power devices (cs.NE).
